# Baalvion code ownership — routes required PR review per bounded context.
# Enforced via branch protection ("Require review from Code Owners").
#
# OWNERSHIP MODEL (current vs target)
# -----------------------------------
# This repository is currently owned by a single GitHub USER account
# (@baalvionservice), NOT an organization. GitHub only resolves *team* handles
# (e.g. @baalvion/platform-core) on organization-owned repos, so every rule
# below is intentionally assigned to @baalvionservice today — that is the only
# identity GitHub can route review to here.
#
# The TARGET structure, once this repo migrates to a GitHub Organization, is the
# per-context team listed in the trailing `# team:` comment on each rule. Restore
# those handles (and create the matching org teams) at migration time; the path
# map below is already the intended layout. Teams should mirror
# Backend/catalog/services/*.yaml `owner`.
#
# Paths follow the federated layout: Backend/services/<domain>/<service>.

# ── Default ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*                                               @baalvionservice   # team: @baalvion/platform-core

